Runtime dependencies
--------------------

In Phase 1 (versions 0.x.y where x < 5), Husk embeds and runs the upstream
Daytona daemon binary inside sandbox containers. The Daytona daemon is
licensed under AGPL-3.0:

  Source:  https://github.com/daytonaio/daytona/tree/main/apps/daemon
  License: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

Husk's control plane communicates with the daemon only over HTTP and never
links its source. Per the FSF's guidance on aggregation
(https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#MereAggregation), this does not
make Husk's source a derivative work of the daemon.

Starting with Husk v0.5, the upstream daemon is replaced by an MIT-licensed
implementation, removing all AGPL components from the runtime.
